15/09/2006
STRUGA, Macedonia -- Macedonian and Albanian border police held a workshop on co-operation Thursday (14 September) in the town of Struga.
The seminar, organised by the OSCE Mission to Skopje, dealt with the strengths and weaknesses of present border patrolling strategies and ways to boost co-operation to combat organised crime.
The participants also discussed way to improve information exchanges and communication.
(OSCE press release, MIA -14/09/06)
